AP-93 Plating
](/markets/unmanned-systems/ap-93-plating)
The first D38999 RoHS compliant 1,000 hour salt spray resistant plating approved by the Defense Logistics Agency (DLA) for the Class AA Qualified Product List (QPL).

High Power 38999
](/markets/unmanned-systems/high-power-38999)
MIL-DTL-38999 Series III connector with RADSOK®, Temper-Grip, or standard high power contacts to accommodate requirements for 500+ amps.

Nimbus Lightweight Hermetic Pin and Socket Connectors
](/markets/unmanned-systems/nimbus)
Nimbus aluminium connectors deliver up to 30% weight reduction compared to traditional stainless-steel designs.

MIL-HD2
](/markets/unmanned-systems/mil-hd2)
The MIL-HD2 is a next-generation VITA and SOSA-aligned VITA 91 connector series designed to achieve 56G PAM4 data rate requirements with higher density.

-------
](/products/mil-hd2)
New High Speed Open Architecture solution for tighter card pitches and chassis designs where space requirements and density are critical.

Aquacon Connectors
](/markets/unmanned-systems/aquacon-connectors)
Amphenol Aquacon connectors have been designed to provide maximum service in oceanic or fluid immersion applications.

Aquacon Hermetic Connectors
](/markets/unmanned-systems/aquacon-hermetic-connectors)
Amphenol Aquacon hermetic connectors are engineered to resist the corrosive environments encountered with oceanic or fluid immersion applications while maintaining a waterproof seal.

38999 Plus
](/markets/unmanned-systems/38999-plus)
Amphenol Aerospace is the industry leader in the design and development of D38999 Series III connectors. While the qualified Mil-Spec versions offer plenty of features, the customization and design options outside of the Mil-Spec are virtually endless.

EMI Filters
](/markets/unmanned-systems/emi-filters)
Filtered connectors provide critical EMI and RFI protection, and can be used on all standard and Mil-spec circular connectors.
